a class="js-wsj-grid-card-author ds2-5-body-sm ds2-5-body-link" data-author-id="170559260" href="https://independent.academia.edu/AnnaVandeBunte">Anna VandeBunte</a></div><p class="ds-related-work--metadata ds2-5-body-xs">Frontiers in digital health, 2022</p><p class="ds2-5-body-sm ds-related-work--abstract ">Wearable Use Among Older Adults including demographics and cognitive functioning. Future studies and clinical providers utilizing wearable activity trackers with older adults may benefit from implementation of reminders (e.g., texts, calls) for device use, particularly among men and individuals with memory impairment.</p><div class="ds-related-work--ctas"><a class="ds2-5-text-link ds2-5-text-link--inline js-tc-loswp--wsj-grid-card-download-pdf-modal js-login-button--93915ded"><span class="material-symbols-outlined" style="font-size: 18px" translate="no">download</span><span class="ds2-5-text-link__content">Download free PDF</span></a><script>document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
